TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: VRAP.RCIT_PRCS_CNTL.PRCS_GID = VRAP.RCIT_REVLD_CLM.PRCS_GID AND VRAP.RCIT_REVLD_CLM.MODEL_TYP_CD = VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_INV.MODEL_TYP_CD AND VRAP.RCIT_REVLD_CLM.INV_ELIG_DT = VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_INV.INV_ELIG_DT AND VRAP.RCIT_REVLD_CLM.CLM_GID = VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_INV.CLM_GID

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: If the process is unable to assign a Period, then the claim will not get updated. This should ONLY occur when the claim is NOT assigned a Rebate ID [implying Model Type=H]
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: RTR_Period_Assigned

GROUP.EXPRESSION:
PRD_ID != 'HOLD'
// If the Period is STILL set to HOLD, that implies that the claim has NOT been assigned a Rebate ID and cannot be updated as NRE.
GROUP.NAME: PeriodAssigned

GROUP.DESCRIPTION: Path for the data when none of the group conditions are satisfied.
GROUP.NAME: DEFAULT1

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: In an attempt to fool Informatica, two ports, PMCY_END_DT and PMCY_TYP_CD are used to do an update, linked to columns INV_ELIG_DT and MODEL_TYP_CD that are not the same. This is done so that these two columns can be updated, yet be used in the WHERE clause to find the claim.
INSTANCE.NAME: RCIT_BASE_CLM_INV_Update

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Update Override
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: UPDATE VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_INV SET INV_ELIG_DT = :TU.INV_ELIG_DT , HOLD_QUE_DT = :TU.HOLD_QUE_DT , PRD_ID = :TU.PRD_ID , NRE_CLM_CD = :TU.NRE_CLM_CD WHERE MODEL_TYP_CD = :TU.MODEL_TYP_CD AND INV_ELIG_DT = :TU.BTCH_DT AND CLM_GID = :TU.CLM_GID
